forskellen på Asynchronous & synchronous callbacks:

Asynchronous code allows the program to be executed immediately where the,
synchronous code will block further execution of the remaining code until it finishes the current one.

if a callback does all it's work before returning to the caller,
it's "synchronous". If it can return to the caller immediately after it's invoked -
and the caller and the callback can work in parallel - then it's "asynchronous"

synkrone kald blokerer tråden, den kan ikke arbejde før den får svar tilbage.
asynkrone svarer inden serveren svarer. fortsætter.